Login into the AWS console 
Click on launch instances, then click next for further steps like tags, storage, configure, etc.
Create a new key pair 
Click on download key pair
click on launch instances
Look on the availability Zone for current running instances
Choose target groups in the side menu
In the target group choose the instance, enter the target group name as any
Click on next, choose the instance 
Click include as pending below
Then click on create target group
Choose load balancer in the side menu
Click Create a load balancer
Choose application load balancer, click create
Type the load balancer name as any
Choose the minimum 2 availability zone(one as same as instance zone)
In listeners and routing, choose the target group that you have created now
Then click on  create a load balancer
The load balancer is created successfully

Open the putty:
In Ubuntu to open putty:(commands)
Ctrl +alt+t  
sudo apt install putty-tools
cd Downloads
sudo puttygen key.pem -o key.ppk -O private
sudo puttygen key.pem -o key.ppk -O public
Sudo chmod  777 key.ppk
Putty
Copy the Public IPV4 address for the currently running instance

Then open the putty and enter the Public IPV4 address of the currently created instance.
In the left menu click SSH, choose Auth, browse the saved file(.ppk) in downloads and click open.
The terminal is open enter accept in pop up
Then enter the command in terminal  ec2-user

Commands in putty:
sudo su
yum install httpd (give yes if asks)
sudo systemctl enable httpd
sudo systemctl start httpd
cd /var/www/html
vim index.html
Copy-paste the HTML document:
Escape:wq  to save the HTML file in putty
Go to security in the left menu, create a security group in that for inbound key type as HTTP and source as anywhere IPV4 and outbound key as all traffic and source as anywhere IPV4
HTTP - destination IP as anywhere IPV4
Outbound - Any traffic - destination IP as anywhere IPV4
Then open the public DNS in the browser, the html file loaded was displayed

